    "It currently contains over 36 million ncRNA sequences integrated from 53 databases.",
    "The AlphaFold Protein Structure Database [25] provides open access to over 200 million protein structure predictions.",
    "Protein Data Bank in Europe (PDBe) [349] and UniProt [350] also provide millions of protein structures.3) Other large-scale biological databases: There are also other large-scale biological databases that are maintained for disease research drug response purposes.",
    "LINCS L1000 dataset [351], which includes information on how different types of human cells respond to various perturbations, such as exposure to drugs, toxins, or genetic modifications.",
    "It measures the expression levels of approximately 1,000 landmark genes, which are carefully selected to represent the entire human genome, on over 41k small molecules."
